http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Woman-held-on-charge-of-abducting-and-killing-baby-boy/article13991292.ece

The Bellur police have arrested a woman on the charges of kidnapping a three-month-old baby boy from Mandya and killing him at Bellur, near Nagamangala in Mandya district.The accused has been identified as Prem Kumari, a native of Gowdarahalli in Channarayapatna taluk of Hassan district.The victim was suffering from heart-related problems and his parents, Arunkumar and Soundarya of B. Hatna village, had brought him to MIMS on January 2. The accused took Shreesha from his grandmother on the pretext of playing with him, but never returned. She later took the boy to a hospital at Bellur and admitted him there, and killed him on January 7, the police said.